latestIgtvVideos.caption:
In the days before the lockdown, the youngest kids of the Free Education Center Innovative Pathshala surprise the team, in which these children had a party for all of us, The whole day had been made, 
It is worth noting that these are the children who make Charkhi for daily food , peel water chestnut, chips making, vegetable selling , the work of Gota soldering in dupattas, daily wages
Poverty so is bound to have to work them together with the parents, which raises the regular food . 
Friends, after spending about 10 to 12 days of their daily wages, these children voluntarily kept this surprise, it is not common, it is a big thing in itself,
In such circumstances, they wants to live their dreams.

Neetu’s Marriage – Part 7: A Dress Full of Dreams

Neetu didn’t have a big designer or family to choose her bridal dress. But she had something even more special — her girls. Her closest friends stood by her side like sisters. They decided to create a dress just for her, inspired by @priyankachopra Chopra’s wedding look.

They spent nights looking at designs, stitching lace, choosing the perfect red. One of them even added tiny hand embroidery with Neetu’s and her fiancé’s names hidden in the veil — just like Priyanka’s!

When Neetu saw the final dress, her eyes filled with tears. It wasn’t just beautiful — it was full of love. Made by hands that truly cared for her. In that moment, she didn’t feel alone anymore.

The dress didn’t come from a fashion label. It came from friendship, from effort, from heart. And that made it priceless.

#NeetuKiShaadi #BridalDressWithLove #InspiredByPriyanka #GirlSupport #RealBrideStory #StrongTogether #desibridemagic

Neetu’s Marriage – Part 6: A Gift from Kajal

On her wedding day, Neetu had no big expectations. But then Kajal, a well-known makeup artist, surprised her. She came with her full kit and a big smile, saying, “Your bridal makeup is my gift.”

Neetu was shocked and deeply touched. Kajal treated her with care and made her feel truly special. When Neetu saw herself in the mirror, she couldn’t hold back her tears.

She looked beautiful — not just because of the makeup, but because someone believed she deserved it.

#NeetuKiShaadi #GiftOfLove #FreeBridalMakeup #KindnessWins #RealBrideStory #SupportAndLove

Neetu’s Marriage – Part 5: A Quiet House

Neetu’s house didn’t feel like home anymore. It was silent, not because it was peaceful, but because no one was there. Her parents were gone. There was no one to help her, no one to talk to. She was all alone.

While other brides had families around, helping them get ready, laughing, doing all the wedding preparations — Neetu did everything by herself. She picked her dress, packed her bags, even chose the wedding songs. No one asked how she was feeling. No one held her hand.

Sometimes, she sat in her room and just stared at the walls. The silence was loud. But still, she didn’t give up. She wiped her own tears, stood up, and kept going. She knew she had to be strong — not because she wanted to, but because she had no choice.

#NeetuKiShaadi #LonelyBride #StrongGirl #SilentTears #WeddingWithoutFamily #EmotionalStory #realfeelings

Neetu Ki Shaadi – Part 3: Mehndi Celebration

The Mehndi ceremony is a festival of colors, music, and joy — a time when the bride shines the brightest.

For Neetu, this celebration was extra special. The girls of Innovation for Change came together to make her mehndi night unforgettable. They danced, laughed, and cheered — turning the day into a true celebration of sisterhood and hope.

With henna on her hands and stars in her eyes, Neetu was the shining bride, surrounded by friends who lifted her up like family.

This was more than just a ceremony. It was a moment of pure happiness, where every girl became a star, and every dance step told a story of love and new beginnings.

Because here, we don’t just celebrate weddings — we celebrate the strength and spirit of every daughter.

#NeetuKiShaadi #MehndiCelebration #InnovationForChange #BeTheFamily #DanceLikeAStar #ShaadiWithDignity #HopeBeginsHer

Neetu Ki Shaadi – Part 2: Haldi Ceremony

The Haldi ceremony is a beautiful tradition filled with love, laughter, and blessings. For Neetu, who grew up without a family, this moment meant more than just rituals — it was about finding a new family.

In this special part of her journey, the girls of Innovation for Change came together to celebrate with her. They applied haldi with warmth and joy, embracing Neetu as their sister.

This wasn’t just about turmeric on the skin — it was about healing old wounds and creating new bonds. It showed Neetu that she belongs, that she is loved, and that she has a family now.

Every bride deserves to feel this love and happiness — and through Neetu Ki Shaadi, we make sure she does.

#NeetuKiShaadi #HaldiCeremony #InnovationForChange #BeTheFamily #ShaadiWithDignity #HopeBeginsHere #supportherjourney
